        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>multicast_timeout_ms</name>
        <qualifiedname>coap_client_request::multicast_timeout_ms</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Multicast response timeout in milliseconds. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>When &gt; 0, indicates a multicast request that accepts multiple responses within the timeout period. After the timeout, a final callback with source=NULL signals completion, after which no further callbacks will be issued. Multicast requests are always non-confirmable (RFC 7252).</para>
<para><simplesect kind="attention"><para>Available only when the following Kconfig option is enabled: <computeroutput>CONFIG_COAP_CLIENT_MULTICAST</computeroutput>. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
